You scored as III - The Empress. The Empress is a maternal symbol. She is the mother figure who loves, nurtures and protects. She will protect you, she will always be there when you are in trouble. When you fall over and graze your knee, the Empress will kiss it better. Yet she is not a weak figure. Her compassion is strength. If her children are threatened she will stop at nothing to protect them. If well aspected in a Tarot spread, the Empress can symbolise security, protection and unconditional love. If badly aspected it can represent over-protectiveness, fear of risk taking and refusal to face the real world.

Although work is difficult and hard on my back already, I'm feeling pretty good. This week I've become more upbeat and happier. Which I'm sure Mike is very happy about. I'm just starting to show now, but can tie it down with several layers for work. I think for them I look like I'm just putting on a bit of weight. 
I was accepted for a mortgage from Scotiabank For $190,000. However, not for the "No Down Payment" thing. Simply because Mike has no Credit ( not bad credit ... just no credit). 
I certainly don't have $10,000 for a down payment and REALLY don't want to be in a one bedroom apartment with no room and an extra person. So the solution... we are going to go to RBC (I've heard that Scotia is quite tight with there money, so hoping that RBC will be more lenient and give use their No Downpayment thing). If whoever that does not work out we will move in to a Co-op for a year or two until Mike credit is Good and they will be BEGGING for use to take their money Moahhhhaaahhhhhaaahhhh!!! ...... Sorry a bit carried away there. 
Anyway Mr. Paul just let us know when you can come down!
 Later.

Alright, so its been a while since i've written anything. I guess its about time. 
Not so much to say i'm afraid.
People say that you shouldn't tell others until you're out of the "danger zone", but so far i've told a lot of people and people on here are pretty much the last to know. 

It turns out that I am with child!
I am 8 weeks right now. 
My due date is December 30th. 

So this puts that house thing a major priority. By Sept we should be moving in to a house. Seeing as I refuse to live in an apartment with a babe, one of the major reasons being space and noise. Noise being my screaming while I go through labor at home where I intent to have my Baby.

I just told the girls at work two days ago. I felt bad that I was slacking and being a touch moody from feeling like shit the past couple weeks, and I've had a manager try to slip that one by me and contrary to what she believed I AM NOT STUPID. They would have caught on anyway. 

I was pretty scared to tell my mom cause I thought she might be mad at me. But she was alright. It doesn't seem like she's very excited about the situation either, but i think once i get past the 3 months and i start to show she'll be more excited. 

Mikes mom was fricking ecstatic it was a bit silly i think but i think it leveled out my moms reaction. 

Well point is I have lots of support and I am happy with the situation, and so is Mike. 

Try to write more often, 
Gwen

So i've decided that it is time for a house, just a starter. 125000. so a 7000 down payment so to save up 10000 for all the expenses of house buying. with good calculations by jan of next year we will have it. ( that's with paying our debt, putting mike through school 450 a semester, and fixing the van at least 1000).  This is as if we are making the same amount of money from now till then. (good old raises)
Yes I have one in mind. It should be in the market around the right time. Its well maintained and has a beautiful backyard.   Its my boss' house.         She has no idea that I have it in mind. and I wont tell her till she puts the house up or maybe as soon as she starts talking about making appointments for Real Estate agents or better yet for an appraiser on the house. If we don't use agents there is no commission  . That would be cool.

I've been watching this show called HUFF. It is my fav new show. you have to check it out. 
time for school work.  
later

BLUES are motivated by INTIMACY, seek opportunities to genuinely connect with others, and need to be appreciated. They do everything with quality and are devoted and loyal friends and employers/employees. Whatever or whomever they commit to are their sole (and soul) focus. They love to serve and will give freely of themselves in order to nurture others lives. BLUES, however, do need to be understood. They have distinct preferences and occasionally the somewhat controlling (but always fair) personality of a confident leader. Their code of ethics is remarkably strong and they expect others to live honest, committed lives as well. They enjoy sharing meaningful moments in conversation as well as remembering special life events (i.e., birthdays and anniversaries). BLUES are dependable, thoughtful, nurturing, and can also be self-righteous, a bit worry-prone, and emotionally intense. They are like sainted pit-bulls who never let go of something once they are committed. When you deal with a BLUE, be sincere, make an effort to truly understand them, and truly appreciate them.

Oh god, Fade to Red (new Tori stuff)is coming out on the 14th and I WWWAAAANNT IIIIITT. If you pre order it its only $19.99, and it has 21 videos and commentary. oooooooowwww. I forwarded the EMail I got to Mike and hopefully he gets the hint. Teehee.

I have the day off again. I find that if I have the too many days off in a row i get tired and lazy. I should go get some food and I should do homework and I should go over to moms house and I should wash my face , and the list goes on. Instead I woke up at 11:00 and I've watched 3 movies, drank tea ate ham with the cat, scratched my self ... thats about it. 
I can't wait to have time go a little faster for work, its always at the beginning that I make mistakes it takes about 5 months for things to settle down. I've been there for about 3 months now, come on 2 more months. These 2 months are the worst 'cause you've been there long enough to know what your doing but you still fuck up more then you feel you should. 
at least life with the "husband" is perfect at home. Going to Chrissie's house really ... well makes my life look perfect. But her baby is beautiful, light brown hair, green eyes, chubby cheeks, smiles so much it buts a light in your heart. 
Babies.
chocolate.
later

So its the little sisters b-day. I called this morning to wish her a happy day but she wasn't even home. that sucks. So i have an addiction. I guess its good that I can confront it, admit it, recognize it, but not sure I can give it up yet. Even though it is making things larger then they should be. That's right CHIPS & DIP. I can't stop I love it I eat it every night. sometimes I'll even eat it instead of a meal. One of the worst parts is, its never good for the BM's, and its gas making too. lol mike wont sit on the couch with me. Just joking. Going to see Chrissie and the babe today. Make sure she's good and hopefully ready to kill that boy of hers. From what I've heard the babe is fat and always happy. 
Been in to this oldies kick lately. Elton John, Paul Simon, The Temptations a lot of 60 and 70's. I'm finding it more fulfilling that any new stuff like system of a down what the hell happened to them they fucking suck now.   
Ah, but remember ... always thinking about babies and chocolate.

Worked today, it was so dead. My co-workers are driving me up the walls, one thinks I have it in for her, are has a grudge against me because she applied for the job i currently hold ( she obviously did get it). 
I signed up for another class Financial Accounting. I have to read the first 2 chapters in the next week, I've already done all the online activities. 
its all kind of mundane the whole waking up going to work doing school fucking your spouse going to sleep waking up and doing it all  again. But every once in a while you get to do something out of the ordinary. Yes ladies and gentlemen its called VACATION. very repetitive. Looking forward to jumping on the couch to relax in my PJ pants and comfy tank and vegging out in front of the tv, good old desperate housewives. 
peace
